# Implementation Plan - Fix Startup Hang on Windows (Comprehensive)

The Paperclip dev server is failing to launch on Windows due to inconsistent use of `127.0.0.1` vs `localhost`. On many Windows systems, `localhost` resolves to the IPv6 address `::1`, while the application and database are partially hardcoded to use the IPv4 address `127.0.0.1`. This leads to connection hangs during database initialization and health checks.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Database Layer
I will update the embedded PostgreSQL connection strings to use `localhost` consistently. This ensures the client can reach the database regardless of whether it binds to IPv4 or IPv6 loopback.

#### [MODIFY] [migration-runtime.ts](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/paperclip/packages/db/src/migration-runtime.ts)
- Switch all embedded connection checks to use `localhost`.

### 2. Server Layer
I will update the default server configuration and its internal connection logic to use `localhost`.

#### [MODIFY] [config.ts](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/paperclip/server/src/config.ts)
- Change default `host` from `127.0.0.1` to `localhost`.

#### [MODIFY] [index.ts](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/paperclip/server/src/index.ts)
- Update embedded database connection strings (lines 342, 404, 410) to use `localhost`.
- Update the default `openHost` (line 670) to use `localhost`.

### 3. Dev Runner & Health Checks
#### [MODIFY] [dev-runner.mjs](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/paperclip/scripts/dev-runner.mjs)
- Update internal health check `fetch` to use `localhost`.

